      - Naming: Test names should read as sentences: should return 401 when token is expired
      - Independence: Each test must be independent — no shared mutable state between tests
      - Determinism: No flaky tests; avoid time-dependent or network-dependent assertions
      - Coverage: Aim for >80% line coverage on business logic; 100% on critical paths (auth, payments)
      - Arrange-Act-Assert: Follow AAA pattern consistently
      - Edge Cases: Always test: empty inputs, boundary values, null/undefined, error paths, concurrent access
      - Avoid: Testing implementation details, over-mocking, testing third-party library internals
      
